refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
intgmp_prob_prime GMPintstringnum intrepetitions10
The function uses Miller-Rabin's probabilistic test to check if a number is a prime.

&reftitle.parameters;




   num



     The number being checked as a prime.

    &gmp.parameter; 



   repetitions



     Reasonable values
     of repetitions vary from 5 to 10 (default being
     10); a higher value lowers the probability for a non-prime to
     pass as a "probable" prime.

    &gmp.parameter;

  &reftitle.examples;



    gmp_prob_prime example


<?php
// definitely not a prime
echo gmp_prob_prime("6") . "\n";

// probably a prime
echo gmp_prob_prime("1111111111111111111") . "\n";

// definitely a prime
echo gmp_prob_prime("11") . "\n";
?>


    &example.outputs;


0
1
2
